          <div class="slide" id="lifestyle1">
            <div class="container">
              <div class="life-style">
                <h1 style="text-decoration: underline" class="whitefont">Eating habits</h1>
                <h4 class="whitefont">Several of the masters in various traditions say that you should eat what you want, just not too much. Below, however, are some considerations from these same traditions that can help people feel confident making positive changes to support their new practice.</h4>
                <h3 class="whitefont">Simple foods, well prepared</h3>
                <h4 class="whitefont">Think for a moment how sugar affects you. You get a burst of mental and physical energy, followed by a trough. Moderating these types of foods seems like a good idea to help keep the mind calm. Start to notice how the food you eat makes you feel.</h4>
                <h3 class="whitefont">72 Labors</h3>
                <h4 class="whitefont">This is a Buddhist practice that considers what work (and by whom) has gone into the meal that has been set in front of you. It can be nice to simply honor that, but it can also be a good way to decide what to eat.</h4>
                <h3 class="whitefont">Moderate alcohol</h3>
                <h4 class="whitefont">In the right circumstances and smaller quantities, alcohol and similar things are fine. Even so, it is best to keep your main practice time free of them if you can.</h4>
              </div>
            </div>
