                <h1 style="text-decoration: underline" class="whitefont"> Vegetarian/Veganism</h1>
                <h4 class="whitefont">Many traditions strongly recommend cutting at least meat and fish out of the diet. It is not expressly necessary, but here are the reasons worth considering for yourself.</h4>
                <h4 class="whitefont"><em>Compassion:</em></h4>
                <h4 class="whitefont">Consuming a diet mainly of plant based ingredients is generally more gentle both from a saving lives standpoint and from a food production standpoint.</h4>
                <h4 class="whitefont"><em>Health:</em></h4>
                <h4 class="whitefont">Adjusting the ratio of animal to plant-based foods to be more on the plant side has many health benefits.</h4>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class='slide' id="lifestyle3">
            <div class="container">
              <div class="life-style">
                <h1 style="text-decoration: underline" class="whitefont">Working Habits</h1>
                <h3 class="whitefont">Work habits</h3>
                <h4 class="whitefont">The ideal is to work thoughtfully without overly identifying with whatever you do.</h4>
                <h3 class="whitefont">What kind of work?</h3>
                <h4 class="whitefont">The kind you feel is good work.</h4>
                <h3 class="whitefont">How much?</h3>
                <h4 class="whitefont">Over-work and under-work have a negative impact on health. Find the place where you feel engaged but not consumed.</h4>
                <h3 class="whitefont">Exercise habits</h3>
                <h4 class="whitefont">Even if your personal practice is not physically demanding, a little regular exercise can go a long way to supporting a developing meditation practice. Something simple like a morning walk would do it.</h4>
